> {{champion:134}} 10/2/4 &quot;but your team carried you...&quot;
> {{champion:157}} &quot;which is why it was ez&quot;

His teammate:

https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/29/Atlas_Schloss_Linderhof.JPG/450px-Atlas_Schloss_Linderhof.JPG
"Did someone say "_**GGEZ**_"??????"

It's called strategy. If you can tilt the opponent and make the game easier for yourself, why not? Nothing about the phrase "gg ez" is against the summoners code. 

This whole cry against Toxicity is a bit extreme, and is being pushed to include banter. Part of the fun of the chat system is the banter!

After my intense-button-mashing-super-skilled-try-hard-sequence of E-Q-W-Repeat on Riven and I type "GG Ez" the enemies always go off, and started fighting each other. Makes for an easier game on my end. {{sticker:zombie-brand-clap}}

Literally the definition of toxic. "I go out ofmy way to do something to upset a fellow player" 
like ?????
{{sticker:zombie-brand-clap}}
